cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image restoration using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel residual dense network architecture, which involves the use of densely connected convolutional layers and local feature fusion. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to the development of new machine learning models and algorithms. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several image restoration tasks, including super-resolution, denoising, compression artifact reduction, and deblurring, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
